"During our subsequent meetings, she told me the story of her search. When she finished, I asked if, one day, I could write it down.
She agreed initially, but whenever we met after that, she kept raising obstacles. She asked me to change the names of those involved; she wanted to know what kind of people would read the book and how they would be likely to react.
'I've no idea,' I said. 'But I don't think that's why you're creating all these problems.'
'You're right,' she said. 'It's because it seems to me such a personal story, and I'm not sure anyone else would get much out of it.'

...Gardeners always recognize one another, because they know that in the history of each plant lies the growth of the whole World."

More or less.

If we have mutual friends, you can figure out where to go from there. If you're creepy, leave me alone.

kthxbai.

"She was back in Ralf Hart's living room, with the fire, the bottle of wine, the two of them sitting on the floor, and everything she had experienced with the English executive the previous night just a dream or a nightmare--depending on how she was feeling. Now she was searching once more for her reason for living, or, rather, for the kind of utter surrender by which a person offers his or her heart and asks for nothing in return."
-Paulo Coelho, Eleven Minutes

"...what really happens at the end is that you sit down and have coffee without looking at each other. There is a sort of strange relief: The thing that was hanging in the air like a gas leak, invisible and toxic, has happened. It's out. It's a relief. It is a solid, tangible. ...[they] are only being peaceful because they know what you don't: that there is no stopping whatever comes next, and so they might as well have coffee while they wait."
(The Center of Winter, Marya Hornbacher)

drown me
in your precious
sense of
innocence

drown me
in words that cut and scream

prick me
with needles
slip and slide into my veins
and hold me
in a false sense
of godlike
superiority

rewrite me
deform me
misshape me
rearrange
me

peel
away
my skin, my flesh, my face
cleanse me
make me something new

pretend, please
that we are just a story
i tell myself
all the time
that i'm not here
that i'm not real
that none of this is happening

i lie.

strange face,
         glass eyes
you're beautiful
you're my doll

   you are not human

you are my
mechanimated
animical
         creation
I dreamed you up
from spiderwebbed lace
and cloud nine
acid
imperfection
holiness
happiness
infection
bliss
 china,
     pewter,
         porcelain
imported
snorted
   grind
   you
   up

dust, my dust
in through windows
like sun
like shadows

if I breathe you in

Sleeping Beauty
  I will
become
  new
and pretty

youre inside me and it hurts get out this time if you will crawling in oceans and salt burns your skin wanna hate something? who knows, you dont want me can i taste something? who knows anything... just once to have you again to fuck you up we're dead again do it again watching you throw up chlorine filled but you're not supposed to be underwater this is not what your lungs breathe drowning in aspirin drowning all for me... drowning all inside of me...

Our bones will never touch.. Drowning in milky ways Stars in my stomach Wash me out Bleed me through I'm nothing, anymore In a world that is without you Existence is so far from here These places where I fade Have long since disappeared So I know I won't escape.. The flesh on bone that's killing us Is slowly sucked away And acid rain will fill me up In moments of decay

I am all your silent liquid voices scream and pale echoes fade softer now lighter lighter pink rose morning thorn and suns like light distant 'cross darkened skies and bled because ashes never fall the ways you seem to believe, want, crawl, asking, asking me . . I am torture in your veins that cried a thousand infinite times rising in a mess of burning flesh and glitter wings so fragile that we're breaking all the time, breaking all we want because that's the only way we'll ever feel a thing
